%% begenone-pkgm-api — Sequence Diagrams
%% Mermaid.js format (.mmd) — use --- to separate multiple diagrams

%% 1. UPLOAD VIDEO FLOW (uploadVideo → uploadVideoMultipart → S3 → Video API)
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant App as App/Consumer
    participant uploadVideo as uploadVideo
    participant multipart as uploadVideoMultipart
    participant AWS as AWS API
    participant S3 as S3
    participant VideoAPI as Video API

    App->>uploadVideo: uploadVideo(file, thumbnail, title, description, token, ...)

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over multipart,S3: Video upload (multipart)
        uploadVideo->>multipart: uploadVideoMultipart(file, filetype: "video")
        multipart->>AWS: POST init multipart (channelId, filetype, mime)
        AWS-->>multipart: { uploadId, key }
        loop For each 10MB chunk
            multipart->>AWS: GET presigned PUT URL (key, uploadId, partNumber)
            AWS-->>multipart: { url }
            multipart->>S3: PUT chunk (presigned URL)
            S3-->>multipart: ETag
        end
        multipart->>AWS: POST complete multipart (key, uploadId, parts)
        multipart-->>uploadVideo: videoKey
    end

    opt thumbnail provided
        uploadVideo->>multipart: uploadVideoMultipart(thumbnail, filetype: "thumbnail")
        multipart->>AWS: init → parts → complete
        multipart-->>uploadVideo: thumbnailKey
    end

    uploadVideo->>VideoAPI: POST create record (title, description, videoKey, thumbnailKey)
    VideoAPI-->>uploadVideo: video data
    uploadVideo-->>App: video data

---
%% 2. WATCH VIDEO FLOW (watchVideo — Video API → Channel API → Video API)
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant App as App/Consumer
    participant watchVideo as watchVideo
    participant VideoAPI as Video API
    participant ChannelAPI as Channel API

    App->>watchVideo: watchVideo(videoId, VIDEO_API_URL, CHANNEL_API_URL, ...)

    watchVideo->>VideoAPI: GET video by ID
    VideoAPI-->>watchVideo: videoData (includes channel ref)

    watchVideo->>watchVideo: Extract channelId from video

    watchVideo->>ChannelAPI: GET channel by ID
    ChannelAPI-->>watchVideo: channelData (name, logo, user)

    watchVideo->>VideoAPI: GET all videos (for recommendations)
    VideoAPI-->>watchVideo: videosData

    watchVideo->>watchVideo: Filter, enrich (timeAgo, thumbnails), shuffle, slice(6)
    watchVideo->>watchVideo: Check subscription, build shareLink, cloudFrontVideoUrl

    watchVideo-->>App: { videoData, cloudFrontVideoUrl, limitedVideos, channelData, ... }

---
%% 3. OVERVIEW / HOME FEED FLOW (getOverview — parallel Video + Channel fetch)
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant App as App/Consumer
    participant getOverview as getOverview
    participant VideoAPI as Video API
    participant ChannelAPI as Channel API

    App->>getOverview: getOverview(VIDEO_API_URL, CHANNEL_API_URL, ...)

    par Parallel fetch
        getOverview->>VideoAPI: GET all videos
        VideoAPI-->>getOverview: videos
    and
        getOverview->>ChannelAPI: GET all channels
        ChannelAPI-->>getOverview: channels
    end

    getOverview->>getOverview: Build thumbnailMap, channelLogoMap
    getOverview->>getOverview: Enrich videos (thumbnailUrl, channelLogoUrl, videoTimeAgo)
    getOverview->>getOverview: Merge featured video, format response

    getOverview-->>App: { data: { videos, featuredVideo } }

---
%% 4. AUTH FLOW (login with rate limiting)
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant App as App/Consumer
    participant login as login
    participant Limiter as Bottleneck
    participant AuthAPI as Auth API

    App->>login: login(email, password, AUTH_API_URL, LOGIN_ENDPOINT)

    login->>Limiter: schedule(request)
    Limiter->>login: (when allowed, minTime: 200ms, maxConcurrent: 1)

    login->>AuthAPI: POST login { eAddress: { email, password } }
    Note right of login: withCredentials: true
    AuthAPI-->>login: { user, token, ... }

    login-->>App: response.data

---
%% 5. VIDEO ENGAGEMENT FLOW (like/dislike/comment/share)
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant App as App/Consumer
    participant engagement as updateVideoInteraction
    participant VideoAPI as Video API

    App->>engagement: updateVideoInteraction(videoId, action, VIDEO_API_URL, ...)
    Note right of App: action: "like" | "unlike" | "dislike" | "undislike"

    engagement->>VideoAPI: PATCH /videos/{videoId}/{action}
    Note right of engagement: withCredentials: true

    alt success
        VideoAPI-->>engagement: { status: "success", likes, dislikes }
        engagement-->>App: { likes, dislikes }
    else error
        VideoAPI-->>engagement: error
        engagement-->>App: throw
    end
